---

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) or use a #garlic press{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2 cm chunks.

Pop the pepper onto a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and slightly charred, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Transfer one-third to a #bowl{} (reserving the rest) and mash with a #fork{}.

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Drain the @grilling cheese{200%g} then cut into slices, 3 per person.

Place the slices into a small bowl of cold water and leave to soak.

> The mashed beans will add a nice thickness to the stew.

Place a large #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, stir in the @harissa paste{1%sachet} and half the garlic. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @chopped tomato with onion & garlic{1%pack} and @water{50%ml}.

Bring to a simmer, then leave to bubble for ~{5%minutes}.

Add the whole and mashed beans. Cook until the stew has reduced slightly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> Add a splash of water to loosen the stew if required.

While the stew simmers, mix the remaining garlic and half the parsley with @oil{1%tbsp} in a small bowl.

Halve the @baguette{2%unit} lengthways.

Using a #spoon{}, rub the herby garlic oil over the cut sides of the baguettes.

Cut the herby baguettes into triangles.

Stir the roasted pepper into the stew along with the remaining parsley. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Pop the baguette onto the (now empty) baking tray and cook on the top shelf of your oven until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove the grilling cheese slices from the cold water and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the cheese and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

Spoon the hearty harissa bean stew into #bowls{}.

Carefully arrange the grilling cheese slices on top.

Serve the garlicky baguette on the side.